article.headline: Cleveland St. 59, Detroit 53 (OT)
article.story: CLEVELAND (AP) -- Ije Nwankwo scored 15 points and gave Cleveland State the lead in overtime as the Vikings beat Detroit 59-53 on Thursday night. J'Nathan Bullock added 10 points in Cleveland State's first conference win (5-8, 1-3 Horizon League) and had the layup that sent the game into overtime at 48. Steve Gansey added 12 points from the bench. The Titans (9-9, 3-2) led 22-17 at the half but were outscored 31-26 in the second half. Cleveland State held Detroit to one basket in overtime and hit five of six free throws in the final 1:04, including two from Nwankwo, who also made the go-ahead layup with 2:33 left. Chuck Bailey had 10 points for Detroit, and Torvoris Baker had 12 rebounds. Detroit was up 44-32 with 7:21 left in regulation, but a jumper by Bullock set off a 14-4 run that tied it with 40 seconds left. Carlos English missed two free throws in the final 10 seconds of regulation for Cleveland State.
